other_tests.findings: Complex mass in the left supraclavicular region, initially measured 4.3 cm in diameter, without internal Doppler flow; repeated scan showed a heterogeneously hypoechoic lesion measuring 4.5 cm suggestive of an evolving hematoma.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Mass size changed from 4.3 cm to 4.5 cm.

other_tests.findings: 5 ml of thin, brown fluid suggestive of old blood, with 104,500 white cells per cubic millimeter, of which 79% were neutrophils; Gram’s staining showed few neutrophils and no organisms.
1.5 ml of thick red fluid consistent with blood; Gram’s staining revealed abundant mononuclear cells and no neutrophils or organisms.
Sinus rhythm, left atrial enlargement, and evidence of old anteroseptal and lateral myocardial infarctions.
Normal subclavian arterial system without extravasation, but evidence of a blush in the area of the mass.
Microscopic examination revealed a mixture of mature tissue types consistent with a diagnosis of mature teratoma; features showed signs of malignancy.
